    "abstract": "<jats:title>Summary</jats:title>\n                <jats:p>\n                  It is unclear whether prior endemic coronavirus infections affect COVID-19 severity. Here, we show that in cases of fatal COVID-19, antibody responses to the SARS-COV-2 spike are directed against epitopes shared with endemic beta-coronaviruses in the S2 subunit of the SARS-CoV-2 spike protein. This immune response is associated with the compromised production of a\n                  <jats:italic>de novo</jats:italic>\n                  SARS-CoV-2 spike response among individuals with fatal COVID-19 outcomes.\n                </jats:p>",
    "DOI": "10.1101/2021.05.04.21256571",
